post: {'type': 'pro', 'text': "But we don't make moral judgements all the time every day. We all need to stop thinking clearly and rationally every now and then, for activities including but not limited to play, fun, pleasure, love, chilling out, taking a load offâ€¦ So all drugs should be legal."}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Recreational drugs can be used as self medication especially for those with severe mental health issues like PTSD and psychosis.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Many poets have made works under the influence of drugs. For example, [the romantic poets used opium and the Beat poets used hallucinogens](https://www.huffingtonpost.com/john-lundberg/drugs-literature-poetry_b_1011124.html).'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'If drugs are cheap and of good quality, there will be no need for people to buy them on the black market.'}

{'type': 'con', 'text': 'Self-medication, for instance with [analgesics](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Analgesic), will worsen the disease and delay proper treatment. So drugs should remain illegal.'}

{'type': 'con', 'text': 'Following legalisation Canada experienced [shortages of cannabis](https://www.independent.co.uk/news/world/americas/canada-marijuana-legal-weed-shortage-pot-running-out-a8593861.html), suggesting that legalisation had caused new individuals to begin using the drug.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'If only leaving syringes was punishable, and not use or possession of drugs, they would put in the extra effort to _not_ break the law at all. I believe all drugs should be legal.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': "Criminalization \\(and incarceration\\) causes lasting harm to a person's health and life outcomes."}
{'type': 'con', 'text': 'Since drug addicts have an impaired sense of \\(rational\\) judgement, drug addiction is detrimental to personal autonomy.'}
{'type': 'con', 'text': 'Legal drugs would not be the only option; there may still be a market of illegal drugs, for example if it is cheaper than the legal choice.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Legalization will allow for effective tools and strategies to fight criminal organizations.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': "Nixon's war on drugs [was started](https://www.cnn.com/2016/03/23/politics/john-ehrlichman-richard-nixon-drug-war-blacks-hippie/index.html) to target blacks and hippies."}
{'type': 'con', 'text': 'This claim is speculative. The correlation between drugs and \\(violent\\) crime is observable. The causes for that correlation are not necessarily observable.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'The government specifies what is unacceptable through prohibition. Taxation is how the government discourages. The government is only "encouraging" if they provide aid or assistance.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'In the long run, the standing of the U.S. government did not suffer from ending the Alcohol Prohibition in the 1930s. Any potential reputational damage from ending marijuana or other prohibitions would be fleeting.'}
{'type': 'con', 'text': 'Drugs can give individuals false perceptions of reality, inducing potentially negative behaviour.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'When obtaining drugs legally people can be sure that the drugs are pure and accurately measured. With the illegal drug market drugs are often mis-sold, inaccurately measured or cut with other substances.'}
{'type': 'con', 'text': 'There is a high level of correlation between [poverty](https://borgenproject.org/addiction-poverty-connected/) and substance abuse.'}

{'type': 'con', 'text': 'An overdose of heroin is usually fatal without medical help; [during 2016](https://www.cdc.gov/drugoverdose/data/heroin.html), almost 15,500 people died from drug overdoses involving heroin in the United States.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Opiates have a [rich history](https://www.history.com/topics/crime/history-of-heroin-morphine-and-opiates) of recreational use, with the Ancient Sumerians calling it "The Joy Plant".'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'The consumption of psychoactive substances creates religious and transcendental [experiences](https://www.sciencealert.com/how-religion-led-to-humanity-s-love-for-drugs): both are a relevant part of human evolution and significantly shaped human culture. I believe all drugs should be legal.'}

{'type': 'con', 'text': "The syntheses for many illicit, addictive and recreational drugs is already known, there would be high amounts of money spent on R&D for new less addictive drugs. That's why drugs should remain illegal."}
{'type': 'con', 'text': "Legalising drugs would be damaging for public health. That's why legalization of drugs is a really bad idea."}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Patients will be able to create, combine or grow their own medicines.'}
{'type': 'con', 'text': "Addiction treatment isn't actually very expensive or costly, and is likely to be clinically simpler to resolve than is widely assumed."}
{'type': 'con', 'text': 'There are often structurally similar legal compounds which can be researched instead of the illegal variation. I believe drugs should remain illegal.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'The government specifies what is unacceptable through prohibition. Taxation is how the government discourages. The government is only "encouraging" if they provide aid or assistance.'}

{'type': 'con', 'text': 'Legalizing marijuana will increase the risk of accidents on the highways \\(and indeed has in [Washington, Oregon and Colorado](http://fortune.com/2018/10/18/legal-marijuana-car-accidents-study/) where it has been legalized\\) causing harm to others.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'In countries where "snus" is legal, the boxes has a compartment for spent product. This would disincetivized and lead to higher penalties if possession was illegal. So all drugs should be legal.'}
{'type': 'con', 'text': '[Personal autonomy](https://www.law.cornell.edu/wex/personal_autonomy) is not a fundamental right in the US constitution.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Drugs being legalized would allow the injured victims \\(or their heirs\\) of fraudulently/irresponsibly cut/marketed drugs to legally and publicly sue the manufacturer/distributor for damages, thereby using market pressures to better assure product/service quality/safety. So all drugs should be legal.'}
{'type': 'con', 'text': 'Legalising strong opioids such as heroin would only exacerbate the opioid crisis.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'US states that have legalised marijuana have seen a lot of benefits.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Taking the stigma and secrecy away from drug taking would mean family and friends would notice drug abuse earlier and be able to intervene.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Drug use is not the same as drug addiction.'}

{'type': 'con', 'text': "A parent's drugs addiction can cause a child to suffer emotional harm and a lack of future stability as it can reduce the parent's life expectancy, causing them to die young. So drugs should remain illegal."}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': "Driving a car or operating machinery while under the influence of drugs is illegal. That's why legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea."}

{'type': 'con', 'text': 'If the primary goal is defeating drug dealing and cartels, the most effective way would be just ceasing drug use by everyone. With the "added bonus" that without drug use people will also be healthier and richer. I think drugs should remain illegal.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Criminals will have to either adapt or lose the income that prevents their other crimes from catching up with them.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'If recreational drugs were legal, social events such as parties would have more variety. Drug-friendly events would also have no cause for paranoia. I think legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': "If you plan to drug someone with the intent of raping them, you're also able to get a hold of the something as ubiquitous as a benzodiazepine."}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'The first [anti-opium laws](http://www.drugpolicy.org/issues/brief-history-drug-war) in the 1870s were directed at Chinese immigrants. I believe all drugs should be legal.'}
{'type': 'con', 'text': 'Allowing people to become addicted merely so we can understand addiction is socially and medically irresponsible. I believe legalization of drugs is a really bad idea.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'A legalization of all drugs may lead to many [replacing](https://theintercept.com/2018/04/20/marijuana-legalization-alcohol-consumption/) part of their alcohol consumption with healthier drugs. So all drugs should be legal.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Many constitutions and legal frameworks promote personal autonomy. I think all drugs should be legal.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': "A society where everyone consumes moderate amounts of drugs wouldn't be much different than the societies of today. That's why legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea."}
{'type': 'con', 'text': 'Pharmaceutical companies could double their revenues by selling harmful and addictive drugs to begin with and subsequently curing medication.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Prohibition does not treat addicts, treatment, and prevention of addiction do. Both of these are accomplished far more effectively without the threat of incarceration for merely admitting use. So all drugs should be legal.'}

{'type': 'con', 'text': "This is an argument of the ends justifying the means. The government could generate more income by simply taking everyone's money by force - that doesn't make it a good choice. I believe legalization of drugs is a really bad idea."}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Legalization will allow people to choose the safer drug. Currently law abiding citizens typically choose alcohol or tobacco which is easily in the more dangerous category.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Drug cartels destabilize Latin America. With legalization they would disappear and Latin America would gain stability.'}
{'type': 'con', 'text': 'Tobacco farming before abolition was [done by slaves](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Tobacco_in_the_American_colonies). So legalization of drugs is a really bad idea.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Many poor people use drugs as a temporary escape from poverty [\\(Scottish Drugs Forum, p. 12\\)](http://www.dldocs.stir.ac.uk/documents/drugpovertylitrev.pdf). Criminalization of this behavior does not help them.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': "Decriminalization would encourage the implementation of a broader scope of impairment detection devices. This would cause users to think twice about driving impaired on substances they believe wouldn't be detected using current methods. I think all drugs should be legal."}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Once you replace the dealers and kingpins of the neighborhoods whose flashy lifestyle would look appealing to naive kids, drugs would lose some of their appeal. So legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea.'}
{'type': 'con', 'text': 'Legalising strong opioids such as heroin would only exacerbate the opioid crisis.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': "When drugs are legalised, people who are addicted may feel more comfortable seeking help and support as they won't be viewed as criminals in the way they currently are. I believe all drugs should be legal."}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'If an individual is already addicted, that would indicate they already have regular access to the drug.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'If recreational drugs were legal, social events such as parties would have more variety. Drug-friendly events would also have no cause for paranoia. I think legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'The illegal trade is already there. The legal trade would just drain their customer base. For criminal trade to survive in those conditions it would have to have either cheaper prices or better product. These are not easily achieved agains big corporations. At least the competition would seriously damage their overheads.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'There have been [no positive consequences](http://fileserver.idpc.net/library/Shadow%20Report_FINAL_ENGLISH.pdf) as a result of the war on drugs. I believe legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': '[Entheogenic drugs](https://maps.org/index.php?option=com_content&view=article&id=5468), such as psychedelics, have been used throughout human history for many benefits in evolutionary growth and cognitive development.'}
{'type': 'con', 'text': "Lots of drug addicts don't want to use drugs, but they can't just simply choose to stop using drugs, because they have an addiction."}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'A [Constitutional Amendment](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Eighteenth_Amendment_to_the_United_States_Constitution) had to be voted on for the prohibition of alcohol. So legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'The legalization of drugs means that they are taken, and disposed of, more safely and cautiously than in the current environment.'}
{'type': 'con', 'text': 'They may lose their job and thus stop contributing to society and paying taxes.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Legalization will remove the taboo that drug addiction currently carries with it. As a result, addicts will no longer be a target of prejudice. I believe legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea.'}

{'type': 'con', 'text': 'Children of addicts may be raised in an environment which makes it [likelier for them](https://www.samhsa.gov/data/sites/default/files/report_3223/ShortReport-3223.html) to consume and become addicts in the future.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': "Taking a more effective approach is not giving up. That's why legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea."}

{'type': 'con', 'text': "This is an argument of the ends justifying the means. The government could generate more income by simply taking everyone's money by force - that doesn't make it a good choice. I believe legalization of drugs is a really bad idea."}
{'type': 'con', 'text': 'Legal drugs would not be the only option; there may still be a market of illegal drugs, for example if it is cheaper than the legal choice.'}

{'type': 'con', 'text': 'Drugs relate with [lower social skills](https://www.gatewayfoundation.org/substance-abuse-treatment-programs/effects-of-drug-abuse/) and antisocial behavior.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': "Tobacco companies are investing in and moving to different technologies \\(vaping\\) as the population becomes more aware of the harms and less prone to tobacco smoking. They can tell tobacco smoking is ultimately a â€˜sinking ship' for their profits."}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Drug use is not the same as drug addiction.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'If the war on drugs were won, these jobs would also be lost.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Legalization could provide valuable data in tracking addicts in early stages when purchasing substances frequently. This could create the opportunity to offer addicts support at earlier stages.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Much of this revenue may be attributed to people who became addicted before they were aware of the negative health consequences. I believe legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea.'}

{'type': 'con', 'text': 'Non-violent dangers could increase, such as syringes being left in parks and other public spaces. This would create a risk of disease and injury to anyone in the area, especially children. I think drugs should remain illegal.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'If psychoactive medicine were properly administered and regulated, it could function in this religious/transcendental function, without causing personal and societal dysfunction. I think legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': '[Incarceration](https://beckleyfoundation.org/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/paper_07.pdf) of drug offenders is expensive and a burden on taxpayers.'}
{'type': 'con', 'text': "Currently, obtaining such drugs is risky, restricted and requires work. Even if they're available, making them freely available may increase the number of rape incidents."}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Drugs are an experience that can build character.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'The legalization of all drugs gives the possibility to control the age group of people participating in the drugs. I think legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': "In a truly free society self regulation should be our privilege. You are free to not use drugs, and you should be just as free to use them. That's why all drugs should be legal."}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Under prohibition, anything related to drugs use \\(like paraphernalia\\) would both be evidence of a crime and likely to be confiscated if found by police â€” this disincentive carrying anything other than the bare necessities to drug use.'}
